From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|lone|lang=enm}}, {{term|lane|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{term|lán||loan|lang=non}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*laihną||that which is lent, loan, fief}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*leykʷ-||to leave, leave over}}. Cognate with {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|lán||loan|lang=is}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|lån||loan|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|lån||loan|lang=da}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Lehen||fief, feudal estate|lang=de}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|leen||fief, feudatory, something lent|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|lien||something borrowed, loan|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|leen||fief, loan, office|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|lane|lang=sco}}, {{term|lain|lang=sco}}, {{term|len||loan|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|læn|lǣn|loan, borrowing, lease, grant, gift, present, benefit|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|lend}}.

